scopecontent.p:
Correspondence and telegrams written principally by constituents pertaining to postal rates, 
                     mail service, and legislation affecting postal workers. Bills concern the status of substitutes, 
                     rural carriers, 
                     special delivery messengers, and star route carriers, particularly relative to Civil Service status; 
                     wages and salaries for various classes of postal warkers; 
                     work week and overtime pay; and paid furloughs. Other material pertains to postal rates, the development of airmail service, and the use by the Post Office of cotton or jute twine. Material is arranged chronologically by month.

